The '''Col de la Cluse''' is a [[mountain pass]] located 1,169 m above sea level in the [[Chartreuse Mountains]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cols-cyclisme.com/chartreuse/france/col-de-la-cluse-depuis-corbel-c653.htm|title=Col de la cluse from Corbel|publisher=cols-cyclisme.com |date= |accessdate=February 26, 2016}}</ref> It connects [[Le Désert d'Entremont]] (commune of [[Entremont-le-Vieux]]) to [[Corbel, Savoie|Corbel]].  The main road of the pass is the D45.

In winter, It is a departure to the [[cross country ski]] slopes. In summer, it is the start of a two-hour hike to access to [[Roche Veyrand]] (1,429 m), overlooking [[Saint-Pierre-d'Entremont, Savoie|Saint-Pierre d'Entremont]] in Savoie .

